N:autoresearch
D:Autonomous ML experimentation framework by Andrej Karpathy. AI agent modifies train.py, runs 5-minute GPU experiments, evaluates with val_bpb, and commits only improvements via git ratcheting for overnight autonomous research.
G:autoresearch ml-experiments autonomous-research karpathy gpu train val-bpb overnight ratcheting

U[5]:
  Set up autoresearch repo on a GPU machine and run first baseline experiment
  Write effective program.md research directives for the autonomous agent
  Run overnight autonomous experiment loop with git ratcheting
  Interpret results.tsv to understand what improvements the agent found
  Configure MAX_SEQ_LEN and EVAL_TOKENS for constrained-VRAM GPUs

S[5]{n,action,details}:
  1,Setup,Install uv; git clone karpathy/autoresearch; uv sync; uv run prepare.py (or bash scripts/setup.sh --seq-len N)
  2,Baseline,Run uv run train.py; grep val_bpb and peak_vram_mb from run.log to confirm setup works
  3,AuthorProgram,Write program.md with goal, current baseline val_bpb, prioritized directions, constraints (VRAM, TIME_BUDGET), and what has already been tried
  4,RunLoop,Point AI agent at repo with program.md context; loop: modify train.py → commit → run 300s → eval → keep/revert → log to results.tsv
  5,Analyze,Use bash scripts/show-results.sh to view improvement timeline, best val_bpb, and experiment statistics

R[5]:
  Never modify prepare.py or constants.py — they define the immutable evaluation harness
  Never change TIME_BUDGET (300s) — this is required for all experiment results to be comparable
  Never add new packages — pyproject.toml is locked; agent can only use what is already installed
  Record what has been tried in program.md to prevent redundant experiments
  Always run check-hardware.sh before a session to verify GPU VRAM and CUDA availability

E[2]{desc,in,out}:
  "Overnight GPU session","bash scripts/run-loop.sh --max 100 --desc session-1","results.tsv with 100 experiments, improvements kept via git ratchet, best val_bpb logged"
  "Hardware check","bash scripts/check-hardware.sh","JSON with gpu_name, vram_mb, cuda_version, ready flag"
